020package org.tquadrat.foundation.javacomposer;
021
022import static org.apiguardian.api.API.Status.DEPRECATED;
023import static org.apiguardian.api.API.Status.STABLE;
024import static org.tquadrat.foundation.lang.Objects.requireNonNullArgument;
025
026import javax.lang.model.type.TypeMirror;
027import java.lang.reflect.Type;
028import java.util.List;
029import java.util.Optional;
030
031import org.apiguardian.api.API;
032import org.tquadrat.foundation.annotation.ClassVersion;
033import org.tquadrat.foundation.javacomposer.internal.TypeNameImpl;
034
035/**
036 *  <p>{@summary The specification for a representation of any type in Java's
037 *  type system, plus {@code void}.} The implementations of this interface
038 *  class are identifiers for primitive types like {@code int} and raw
039 *  reference types like
040 *  {@link String}
041 *  and
042 *  {@link java.util.List List}.
043 *  It also identifies composite types like
044 *  {@code char[]}
045 *  and
046 *  {@link java.util.Set Set&lt;Long&gt;}.</p>
047 *  <p>Type names are dumb identifiers only and do not model the values they
048 *  name. For example, the type name for {@code java.lang.List} doesn't know
049 *  about the
050 *  {@link java.util.List#size() size()}
051 *  method, the fact that lists are collections, or even that it accepts a
052 *  single type parameter.</p>
053 *  <p>Instances of this class are immutable value objects that implement
054 *  {@link Object#equals(Object) equals()}
055 *  and
056 *  {@link Object#hashCode()}
057 *  properly.</p>
058 *
059 *  <h2>Referencing existing types</h2>
060 *  <p>Primitives and {@code void} are constants that can be referenced directly:
061 *  see for example
062 *  {@link Primitives#INT},
063 *  {@link Primitives#DOUBLE},
064 *  and
065 *  {@link Primitives#VOID}.</p>
066 *  <p>In an annotation processor, a type name instance for a type mirror can
067 *  be obtained by calling
068 *  {@link #get(TypeMirror)}.
069 *  In reflection code,
070 *  {@link #get(Type)}
071 *  can be used.</p>
072 *
073 *  <h2>Defining new types</h2>
074 *  <p>New reference types like {@code com.example.HelloWorld} can be created
075 *  with
076 *  {@link ClassName#from(CharSequence,CharSequence,CharSequence...)}.
077 *  To build composite types like {@code char[]} and {@code Set<Long>}, the
078 *  factory methods on
079 *  {@link ArrayTypeName},
080 *  {@link ParameterizedTypeName},
081 *  {@link TypeVariableName},
082 *  and
083 *  {@link WildcardTypeName}
084 *  should be used.</p>
085 *
086 *  @author Square,Inc.
087 *  @modified Thomas Thrien - thomas.thrien@tquadrat.org
088 *  @version $Id: TypeName.java 997 2022-01-26 14:55:05Z tquadrat $
089 *  @since 0.0.5
090 *
091 *  @UMLGraph.link
092 */
093@ClassVersion( sourceVersion = "$Id: TypeName.java 997 2022-01-26 14:55:05Z tquadrat $" )
094@API( status = STABLE, since = "0.0.5" )
095public sealed interface TypeName
096    permits ArrayTypeName, ClassName, ParameterizedTypeName, TypeVariableName, WildcardTypeName, TypeNameImpl
097{
098        /*---------*\
099    ====** Methods **==========================================================
100        \*---------*/
101    /**
102     *  Creates a new instance for an implementation of {@code TypeName} as a
103     *  copy of this one, but with the given annotations added.
104     *
105     *  @param  annotations The annotations.
106     *  @return The new instance.
107     */
108    public default TypeName annotated( final AnnotationSpec... annotations )
109    {
110        return annotated( List.of( requireNonNullArgument( annotations, "annotations" ) ) );
111    }   //  annotated()
112
113    /**
114     *  Creates a new instance for an implementation of {@code TypeName} as a
115     *  copy of this one, but with the given annotations added.
116     *
117     *  @param  annotations The annotations.
118     *  @return The new instance.
119     */
120    public TypeName annotated( final List<AnnotationSpec> annotations );
121
122    /**
123     *  Returns the array component for the given type name; the return value
124     *  is empty if the given type is not an array.
125     *
126     *  @param  type    The type name.
127     *  @return An instance of
128     *      {@link Optional}
129     *      that holds the type name of the array component.
130     */
131    @SuppressWarnings( "ClassReferencesSubclass" )
132    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.0.5" )
133    public static Optional<TypeName> arrayComponent( final TypeName type )
134    {
135        return type instanceof ArrayTypeName arrayType ? Optional.of( arrayType.componentType() ) : Optional.empty();
136    }   //  arrayComponent()
137
138    /**
139     *  Returns the given type name as an array; the return value is empty if
140     *  it is not an array.
141     *
142     *  @param  type    The type name.
143     *  @return An instance of
144     *      {@link Optional}
145     *      that holds the array type name.
146     */
147    @SuppressWarnings( {"ClassReferencesSubclass", "StaticMethodOnlyUsedInOneClass"} )
148    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.0.5" )
149    public static Optional<ArrayTypeName> asArray( final TypeName type )
150    {
151        final var retValue = TypeNameImpl.asArray( type ).map( a -> (ArrayTypeName) a );
152
153        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
154        return retValue;
155    }   //  asArray()
156
157    /**
158     *  Returns a boxed type if this is a primitive type (like
159     *  {@link Integer}
160     *  for {@code int}) or {@code void}. Returns this type if boxing doesn't
161     *  apply.
162     *
163     *  @return The boxed if necessary, otherwise this.
164     */
165    public TypeName box();
166
167    /**
168     *  {@inheritDoc}
169     */
170    @Override
171    public boolean equals( final Object o );
172
173    /**
174     *  Returns a type name equivalent to that from the given
175     *  {@link TypeMirror}
176     *  instance.
177     *
178     *  @param  mirror  The given type mirror instance.
179     *  @return The respective type name.
180     */
181    @SuppressWarnings( "ClassReferencesSubclass" )
182    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.2.0" )
183    public static TypeName from( final TypeMirror mirror )
184    {
185        final var retValue = TypeNameImpl.from( mirror );
186
187        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
188        return retValue;
189    }   //  from()
190
191    /**
192     *  Returns a type name equivalent to that of the given
193     *  {@link Type}
194     *  instance.
195     *
196     *  @param  type    The type.
197     *  @return The respective type name for the given {@code Type} instance.
198     */
199    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.2.0" )
200    public static TypeName from( final Type type ) { return TypeNameImpl.from( type ); }
201
202    /**
203     *  Returns a type name equivalent to that from the given
204     *  {@link TypeMirror}
205     *  instance.
206     *
207     *  @param  mirror  The given type mirror instance.
208     *  @return The respective type name.
209     *
210     *  @deprecated Use
211     *      {@link #from(TypeMirror)}
212     *      instead.
213     */
214    @Deprecated( since = "0.2.0", forRemoval = true )
215    @API( status = DEPRECATED, since = "0.0.5" )
216    public static TypeName get( final TypeMirror mirror ) { return from( mirror ); }
217
218    /**
219     *  Returns a type name equivalent to that of the given
220     *  {@link Type}
221     *  instance.
222     *
223     *  @param  type    The type.
224     *  @return The respective type name for the given {@code Type} instance.
225     *
226     *  @deprecated Use
227     *      {@link #from(Type)}
228     *      instead.
229     */
230    @Deprecated( since = "0.2.0", forRemoval = true )
231    @API( status = DEPRECATED, since = "0.0.5" )
232    public static TypeName get( final Type type ) { return from( type ); }
233
234    /**
235     *  {@inheritDoc}
236     */
237    @Override
238    public int hashCode();
239
240    /**
241     *  Checks whether this type name is annotated.
242     *
243     *  @return {@code true} if it is annotated, {@code false} otherwise.
244     */
245    public boolean isAnnotated();
246
247    /**
248     *  Checks whether this type name represents a box primitive type.
249     *
250     *  @return {@code true} if this is a boxed primitive type like
251     *      {@link Integer}.
252     *      {@code false} for all other types including unboxed primitives and
253     *      {@link java.lang.Void}.
254     */
255    public boolean isBoxedPrimitive();
256
257    /**
258     *  Checks whether this type name represents a primitive type.
259     *
260     *  @return {@code true} if this is a primitive type like {@code int}.
261     *      {@code false} for all other types including boxed primitives and
262     *      {@code void}.
263     */
264    public boolean isPrimitive();
265
266    /**
267     *  {@inheritDoc}
268     */
269    @Override
270    public String toString();
271
272    /**
273     *  Returns an unboxed type if this is a boxed primitive type (like
274     *  {@code int} for
275     *  {@link Integer})
276     *  or {@code Void}. Returns this type if it is already unboxed.
277     *
278     *  @return The unboxed type if applicable, or this.
279     *  @throws UnsupportedOperationException   This type isn't eligible for
280     *      unboxing.
281     */
282    public TypeName unbox();
283
284    /**
285     *  Creates a new instance for an implementation of {@code TypeName} as a
286     *  copy of this one, but without any annotations.
287     *
288     *  @return The new instance.
289     */
290    public TypeName withoutAnnotations();
291}
292//  interface TypeName
